        "Built by Jerome B. Wheeler in 1889 , this Aspen landmark was one of the first buildings west of the Mississippi to have full electric lighting . Its ballroom is the only one in Aspen above ground . In the later 20th century it became one of the city 's first celebrity hangouts - Hunter Thompson used the downstairs J-bar as his de facto office during the days , and it hosted an active party and drug scene at night",
